* 2x Openings
*Description* In third seat the opening are wide ranging (both in shape and range)\\
First and second seat vulnerable the opening are fairlly standard weak two, agressive but tend to always have a 6 card suit\\
First and second seat not vulnerable the openings show 7 to 10 points and a five card or longer suit. We tend to almost never upgrade 5/6 counts into this opening.\\
With a 6 card suit with no side suit honors we prefer to open at the 3 level, so that that a not vulnerable 2 level opening is either from a 5 card suit or has at least a side suit Q\\
This is important as the style is to for partner to agressively look to penalize oppenents (so do not be tempeted to open xx KQJxxx xxx xx at the two level)\\
They tend to deny 4 card majors (unless in a 6/4 with a good primary suit and bad major).\\
Not vulnerable the is no further requirment on the opening, the suit could be Jxxxx, and it could be from a 5332 distribution\\
If don't feel comftable opening this hands, don't play the system in the first place.\\

2NT Ogust:
- 3!c :: 5x min
- 3!d :: 6x min
- 3!h :: 5x max
- 3!s :: 6x max

When vulnerable 3!c/3!d show a bad 6 card suit and 3!d/!s good 6 card suits\\

Over 2!c opening the ask is 2!d with the same min/min/max/max responses.\\

Two level new suits are NF but expect to be raise with 3 card support (2NT with 3 card support and a max)\\
3 level suit (with or with out jump) are natural GF (generally 6+suits)\\

** Competition
If the overcall doubles are penalties\\
If they double new suits are NF and XX is strong looking for penalties (opener is expected to double if he has 3 cards in the suit they run to)\\

2NT is always kept as Ogust (Over a 2!c opening 2NT becomes the Ogust ask as well)

