** XY2Z
After 1m - 1M if opener rebids a nonforcing 2m, and there is at least one free step below 2 in our major we play something similar to XYZ:\\
XY2Z is played after:\\
1!c - 1M\\
2!c - ?\\

1!d - 1!s\\
2m - ?\\

1!d - 1!s\\
1NT - 2!c\\
2!d - ?\\

In all this sequences we use 2M-1 to show either a weak hand with 6+M or any invitational hand. While (almost)all other bids are natural and GF.\\
1!c-1!h-2!c
- 2!d :: 6+!h weak or any inv
- 2!h :: 4+!h generic GF
- 2!s :: (semi natural) GF
- 2NT :: balanced GF
- 3!c :: 4+!c GF
- 3!d :: 5+!d-4+!h GF
- 3!h :: solid 6+!h GF

1!c - 1!s - 2!c
- 2!d :: *ALEEERT* 4+!h inv+
- 2!h :: 6+!s weak or any inv(no 4!h)
- 2!s :: 4+!s generic GF
- 2NT :: balanced GF
- 3!c :: 4+!c GF
- 3!d :: 5+!d GF
- 3!h :: 5-5 GF
- 3!s :: solid 6+!s GF

1!d - 1!s - 2!c
- 2!d :: s.o.
- 2!h :: 6+!s weak or any inv
- 2!s :: 4+!s generic GF
- 2NT :: balanced GF
- 3!c :: 4+!c GF
- 3!d :: 4+!d GF
- 3!h :: 5-5 GF
- 3!s :: solid 6+!s GF

1!d - 1!s - 2!d (5+!d-3!s)
- 2!h :: weak (4)5!s or any invite
- 2!s :: GF 5+!s
- 2NT :: 4!s balanced GF
- 3!c :: 4!s 4SF GF
- 3!d :: 4!s 3+!d GF

and similarly after 1!d - 1!s - 1NT - 2!c - 2!d\\

Note that we do not play XY2Z after 1!d-1!h-2!c, yes the is 2!d available, but is used as natural non forcing and we simply use 2!s as 4SF GF.\\
